summary: CommScope's innovation in DOCSIS 4.0, soaring Access Network sales and portfolio shifts keep momentum strong.

headline: 3 Reasons to Sell GLW and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Corning’s 39.7% return over the past six months has outpaced the S&P 500 by 29.2%, and its stock price has climbed to $67.43 per share. This was partly thanks to its solid quarterly results, and the performance may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
